ALICE will need upgrade of its fibre network in LS2, with the addition of ~20k fibres between the cavern and the counting room on the surface. The need for this upgrade arises from the installation of new detectors and the read-out upgrade of existing detectors. All fibres will be multi-mode fibres. The data transfer between the cavern and the counting room will nominally operated at 4.8 Gb/s. However, the choice of fibres needs to allow an operation of 10 Gb/s for possible future upgrades.

A new ALICE Online/Offline computing farm, namely O2, will be installed at P2 before LS2. The computing part of the farm will require a new room (CR0). CR0 will require 2MW electrical power (with an option of adding 500 kW). The EL and CV modifications should be done during the EYETS at latest. The facility should be available in Q2/18, and operational (full load) by 9/18. We ask EN-EL to also modify the present 500kVA UPS distribution, by bringing a quota of this power to CR0

This project will be maintained (and if so it will probably be anticipated during YETS) only in case GreenCube won't be done anymore. An initial study was already done by J. Pierlot. CR0 will be in surface and will host majority of the O2 data center. Most of the 500kVA issued by the UPS in SX (currently supplying loads in CR1 and CR2) will be re-routed to CR0 (the re-routing should be done necessarily during LS2, as UPS needed during RUN).
